"a.被鼓动的；不安的 【英】 adj.被鼓动的(excite d)；不安的(perturbed) 【考】 literate : erudite / agitated : frenetic(博学是非常有文化/ 狂乱是非常不安)abandon : inhibition / tranquility : agitation(放纵无抑制/宁静无 躁动)反义词：equanimity( 镇静)-agitation (n. 鼓动；焦虑) 【记】 ag(做)+itate(表示不 断的动作)→不断地做 →鼓动; 【同】 派生词: agitation (n. 鼓动；焦虑) 【例】 The agitated monkey pounded on the wall. adj. 被鼓动的 = excited; 焦虑的, 不安的 = perturbed 【记】ag做, it动物的它, ate吃的过去式－把小动物作来吃, 那么它的心情一定是－非常焦虑不安 【类】literate: erudite = agitated: frenetic非常有文化是博学的 = 非常不安是狂乱的abandon: inhibition = tranquility: agitation放纵不会抑制 = 宁静不会躁动 【记】age- 驱使，做，近于agent agitated (adj.)  1610s, ""set in motion,"" past participle adjective from agitate (v.). Meaning ""disturbed"" is from 1650s; that of ""disturbed in mind"" is from 1756. Meaning ""kept constantly in public view"" is from 1640s."
